{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.38",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 38,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 38",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 38 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:1",
      "text": "Then the Lord answered Job out of the whirlwind:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:2",
      "text": "“Who is this that darkens counsel by words without knowledge?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:3",
      "text": "Gird up your loins like a man, I will question you, and you shall declare to me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:4",
      "text": "“Where were you when I laid the foundation of the earth? Tell me, if you have understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:5",
      "text": "Who determined its measurements—surely you know! Or who stretched the line upon it?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:6",
      "text": "On what were its bases sunk, or who laid its cornerstone,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:7",
      "text": "when the morning stars sang together, and all the sons of God shouted for joy?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:8",
      "text": "“Or who shut in the sea with doors, when it burst forth from the womb;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:9",
      "text": "when I made clouds its garment, and thick darkness its swaddling band,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:10",
      "text": "and prescribed bounds for it, and set bars and doors,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:11",
      "text": "and said, ‘Thus far shall you come, and no farther, and here shall your proud waves be stayed’?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:12",
      "text": "“Have you commanded the morning since your days began, and caused the dawn to know its place,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:13",
      "text": "that it might take hold of the skirts of the earth, and the wicked be shaken out of it?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:14",
      "text": "It is changed like clay under the seal, and it is dyed like a garment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:15",
      "text": "From the wicked their light is withheld, and their uplifted arm is broken.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:16",
      "text": "“Have you entered into the springs of the sea, or walked in the recesses of the deep?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:17",
      "text": "Have the gates of death been revealed to you, or have you seen the gates of deep darkness?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:18",
      "text": "Have you comprehended the expanse of the earth? Declare, if you know all this.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:19",
      "text": "“Where is the way to the dwelling of light, and where is the place of darkness,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:20",
      "text": "that you may take it to its territory and that you may discern the paths to its home?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:21",
      "text": "You know, for you were born then, and the number of your days is great!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:22",
      "text": "“Have you entered the storehouses of the snow, or have you seen the storehouses of the hail,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:23",
      "text": "which I have reserved for the time of trouble, for the day of battle and war?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:24",
      "text": "What is the way to the place where the light is distributed, or where the east wind is scattered upon the earth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:25",
      "text": "“Who has cleft a channel for the torents of rain, and a way for the thunderbolt,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:26",
      "text": "to bring rain on a land where no man is, on the desert in which there is no man;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:27",
      "text": "to satisfy the waste and desolate land, and to make the ground put forth grass?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:28",
      "text": "“Has the rain a father, or who has begotten the drops of dew?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:29",
      "text": "From whose womb did the ice come forth, and who has given birth to the hoarfrost of heaven?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:30",
      "text": "The waters become hard like stone, and the face of the deep is frozen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:31",
      "text": "“Can you bind the chains of the Pleiades, or loose the cords of Orion?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:32",
      "text": "Can you lead forth the Mazzaroth in their season, or can you guide the Bear with its children?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:33",
      "text": "Do you know the ordinances of the heavens? Can you establish their rule on the earth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.34",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:34",
      "text": "“Can you lift up your voice to the clouds, that a flood of waters may cover you?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.35",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:35",
      "text": "Can you send forth lightnings, that they may go and say to you, ‘Here we are’?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.36",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:36",
      "text": "Who has put wisdom in the clouds, or given understanding to the mists?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.37",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:37",
      "text": "Who can number the clouds by wisdom? Or who can tilt the waterskins of the heavens,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.38",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:38",
      "text": "when the dust runs into a mass and the clods cleave fast together?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.39",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:39",
      "text": "“Can you hunt the prey for the lion, or satisfy the appetite of the young lions,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.40",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:40",
      "text": "when they crouch in their dens, or lie in wait in their covert?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.38.41",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:41",
      "text": "Who provides for the raven its prey, when its young ones cry to God, and wander about for lack of food?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
